# 2. AI vs. Non-AI Labeling

::: {#ai-labeling .cell execution_count=2}
``` {.python .cell-code code-summary="Classify each posting as AI-Related or Non-AI"}
ai_keywords = [
    r'\bai\b', r'artificial intelligence', r'machine learning', r'\bml\b',
    r'deep learning', r'neural network', r'\bnlp\b', r'natural language processing',
    r'computer vision', r'data scien', r'reinforcement learning',
    r'generative ai', r'\bgpt\b', r'\bllm\b', r'large language model',
    r'robotics', r'autonomous', r'predictive model', r'tensorflow',
    r'pytorch', r'chatbot', r'intelligent automation'
]
ai_pattern = '|'.join(ai_keywords)

# Build search text from title + ONET occupation + skills list
search_text = (
    df['title_name'].fillna('').str.lower() + ' ' +
    df['onet_name'].fillna('').str.lower() + ' ' +
    df['skills_name'].apply(lambda lst: ' '.join(lst).lower() if isinstance(lst, list) else '')
)

df['is_ai'] = search_text.str.contains(ai_pattern, case=False, na=False)
df['job_category'] = df['is_ai'].map({True: 'AI-Related', False: 'Non-AI'})

counts = df['job_category'].value_counts()
print(f"AI-Related:  {counts.get('AI-Related', 0):,} ({df['is_ai'].mean()*100:.1f}%)")
print(f"Non-AI:      {counts.get('Non-AI', 0):,} ({(1-df['is_ai'].mean())*100:.1f}%)")
```

::: {.cell-output .cell-output-stdout}
```
AI-Related:  11,727 (16.2%)
Non-AI:      60,727 (83.8%)
```
:::
:::


