### Labeling Takeaway

The share of AI-related postings in our Lightcast data closely mirrors what we see at the national level. For example, the Stanford AI Index shows that the share of U.S. job postings requiring AI skills increased from 1.4% in 2023 to 1.8% in 2024. Similarly, UMD-LinkUp AI Maps found that AI-related postings grew by 68% between Q4 2022 and Q4 2024.
Our keyword-based approach picks up on the same trend. Even though AI jobs still make up a relatively small portion of the overall labor market, they are growing quickly. This makes the geographic patterns we observe especially important: AI hiring isn’t evenly distributed, but instead tends to cluster in a handful of states and metro areas.

---

# 3. Geographic Analysis

## 3.1 Top States by AI Job Volume

::: {#cell-state-volume .cell execution_count=4}
