### Choropleth Takeaway

The choropleth map makes the geographic pattern easier to see: AI job intensity is concentrated in a relatively small set of states rather than spread evenly across the country. The strongest cluster appears in the Northeast and Mid-Atlantic, especially around DC, Maryland, Virginia, New Jersey, New York, Massachusetts, and Connecticut. Washington also stands out on the West Coast, while much of the Midwest, Southeast, and interior West shows lower AI intensity.
Overall, the map supports the broader finding that AI hiring is tied to innovation-heavy labor markets, where research institutions, federal contractors, technology firms, and professional services employers are more concentrated.

