This pattern is independently corroborated by Bureau of Labor Statistics data. In 2024, the three states with the largest absolute job gains were Texas (+284,200), California (+180,500), and Florida (+147,900). But the fastest *percentage* growth occurred in Idaho (+3.6%), Missouri (+2.8%), and South Carolina (+2.8%) — none of which are top AI states. Texas is the notable outlier: it ranks among the very top for both AI job creation (UMD-LinkUp) and total employment growth (BLS), making it the clearest example of a state that bridges both labor market tracks.

